  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>sweet potatoes</strong>&nbsp;(skins on) into&nbsp;thick rounds</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>rounds</strong>&nbsp;to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Give everything a good old mix up and put the tray in the oven for 15 min (approx. step 4)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aubergine-sweet-potato-yasai-curry/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel the<strong> ginger</strong> and slice&nbsp;half of it&nbsp;into matchsticks (save the rest for later!)</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> rice vinegar</strong> to a large mixing bowl&nbsp;with 2 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\r\n<p>Stir until the <strong>sugar</strong> has dissolved, then add the&nbsp;<strong>ginger&nbsp;matchsticks</strong> and set aside to pickle</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aubergine-sweet-potato-yasai-curry/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim the <strong>green stalk<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> from the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and cut into quarters lengthways&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> aubergine</strong> and cook for 2 min on each flesh side until browned</p>\r\n<p>Transfer the <strong>aubergine</strong> to the tray with the&nbsp;<strong>sweet potato</strong>&nbsp;and return it to the oven for 15-20 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aubergine-sweet-potato-yasai-curry/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reserve the pan</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aubergine-sweet-potato-yasai-curry/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice the<strong>&nbsp;shallots&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel the&nbsp;<strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;then continue to peel lengths of&nbsp;carrot&nbsp;until you end up with a pile of&nbsp;carrot 'ribbons'</p>\r\n<p>Once you cannot peel any more, grate the remaining<strong>&nbsp;carrot</strong></p>\r\n<p>Finely chop (or grate) the remaining&nbsp;<strong>ginger&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aubergine-sweet-potato-yasai-curry/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of<strong>&nbsp;vegetable oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong>&nbsp;chopped shallot</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>chopped ginger</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>grated carrot</strong>&nbsp;and <strong>curry powder</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3 min</p>\r\n<p>Stir 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>&nbsp;into the pan cook for 1 min</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aubergine-sweet-potato-yasai-curry/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> to the pan, then add the <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>mango chutney</strong> and <strong>nigella seeds</strong></p>\r\n<p>Whisk to combine and cook for 5-7 min or until the sauce has thickened &ndash; this is your <strong>curry sauce</strong></p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, trim then slice the <strong>spring onions</strong>&nbsp;finely</p>\r\n<p>Bash the <strong>roasted peanuts</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until finely crushed (keep them in the bag so you don't lose any!)</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aubergine-sweet-potato-yasai-curry/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong>, <strong>crushed peanuts</strong>, <strong>carrot ribbons</strong> and<strong>&nbsp;baby leaf salad</strong> to the large bowl of <strong>pickled ginger</strong> and mix to combine &ndash; this is your <strong>Japanese salad</strong></p>\r\n<p>Serve the<strong>&nbsp;aubergine</strong> and<strong> sweet potato&nbsp;</strong>with<strong>&nbsp;</strong>the<strong>&nbsp;</strong>cooked <strong>rice</strong> and<strong>&nbsp;Japanese salad</strong> to the side&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Spoon the <strong>curry sauce</strong> all over the <strong>vegetables </strong>and enjoy!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
